/*
   $VER: AutoArrangeIcons 47.1 (28.09.2020)

   Updates, resizes, sorts and snapshots the active window.
   
   For those of us who constantly swap icons and/or install lots of 
   programs and rearrange its icon positions, this is really handy.
   
   This is a set of two ARexx scripts that when the [Right Amiga] + Y
	 keys are pressed, they update and resize the active window, 
	 sorting its icons by name, to later "snapshot all" of them.
   
   A menu item under the "Tools" menu is available for this purpose 
   too.
*/

ADDRESS WORKBENCH

MENU ADD NAME '"AUTOARRANGEICONS"' TITLE '"Auto-arrange Icons"' SHORTCUT "Y" CMD "S:AutoArrangeIcons.rexx"